# === register_pair.4004 ===
# Load an 8-bit immediate into a register pair via FIM (Fetch IMmediate).
# The 4004 stores register pairs as {even-numbered: high nibble,
# odd-numbered: low nibble}, so FIM P0, 0x35 fills R0 with 3 and R1
# with 5.
#
# This is one of the 4004's five 2-byte instructions; the assembled
# program below has 2 bytes for one logical instruction.
#
# After execution:
#   ACC = 0
#   R0  = 3   (high nibble of 0x35)
#   R1  = 5   (low nibble of 0x35)

20   # FIM P0    Pair-0 fetch-immediate: opcode byte
35   #           Immediate data byte: high=3 -> R0, low=5 -> R1
